description.narrative: The second phase of the Recognised Seasonal Employer (RSE) worker training programme provides English, numeracy and life-skills training to at least 1,200 Pacific RSE workers annually in the Bay of Plenty, Hawkes Bay, Nelson, Marlborough, Northland, Waikato, Wairarapa and Central Otago. The training is learner-led and will maximise the development benefits of the RSE policy in the Pacific by providing RSE workers with access to skills training during their time in New Zealand.
